when i drive, i get this nervous feeling in my gut that a cop is going to pull me over and make me take a driving test all over again.

i'm amazed at the ease at which i got my license, no wonder we have so many car accidents and so many crazy people on the roads. all you have to do is a three point turn and back straight. i hadn't done a single three point turn until my driving test.

and she said it was the best three point turn of the week.  sweet.

Its so hard to know that everything I'm watching is changing, gradually. And when I look at everyone elses lives, and see their change I don't know how they cope with it, how do people continue with the knowledge of everything not being secure.  I know that in two years my sister will not be living with me, and we will spend six months away from each other-there will be an entire ocean in between us, and I know that in two years I will be going to college, and expecting the same great things I have seen Stephanie experience. But I know that I will be let down, because the college experiences that I will be expecting have already happened. The people that I was around most of middle school and high school, the people that you're suppose to be with during these college experiences  have already been there and done that.

I guess that I am finally realizing that I'm about to take the biggest step of life that I have ever taken.

And ' I've got this feeling that there is something that I missed ', when I was growing up with Stephanie and Ryan and Adam. I feel like there was that space in time when I was suppose to find my Ryan and my Adam, but I didn't because I was with the Ryan and Adam that I knew, the three of them leaving for college just wasn't something that I grasped.

Big Step.

' I can do most anything '. I can find this in people my age, I can find genuine openess, genuine happiness.

This is the strong part of being strong.

' This could be the very moment I realize that I am alive, all these places feel like home '

Your Birthdate: April 27 
Your birth on the 27th day of the month (9 energy) adds a tone of selflessness and humanitarianism to your life path. 
Certainly, you are one who can work very well with people, but at the same time you need a good bit of time to be by yourself to rest and meditate. 
There is a very humanistic and philanthropic approach in most of things that you do. 

This birthday helps you be broadminded, tolerant, generous and very cooperative. 
You are the type of person who uses persuasion rather than force to achieve your ends.
You tend to be very sensitive to others' needs and feelings, and you able to give much in the way of friendship without expecting a lot in return.

we are all going through changes
good and bad
and that dosnt mean we are weak
or that we have no life

we're just all coming together 
into our lives 
and into each others lives

that i fell out of his life 
and into all the lives 
i have fallen into

but when i think about it
i smile.

but im learning to deal with it. 
because at the end of the day, 
when i have to put you to bed,
i ask myslef why i even came down to check on you.

you're always in the same state. 

and when i make plans with you, 
and your friends call,
the friends that feed you along with this crap,
i ask myself why i did this.

and then i remeber.

the times you're not like this
are the times i love you most
and when you are not around them
its obvious to everyone 
that you are better than that.
                               you are better than them.

i just wish that i could help you
because in some odd way you have never been more
beautiful
more lucky
or more full of love
and life.

but i know that if i keep trying to help you
if i keep repeating my steps
                              i am stuck in the exact same place you are
and after three years of this relationship with you
listening to you complain
and guilt me into everything
and string me along

im ready to take different steps
and do my thing
and i know that if i am lucky
and if you are meant to go futher than this
someday 
someone
besides me
will notice, and take it in to thought.

and that would be the most amazing day of my life.
because i miss you more than i miss the things that you took away from me.

And I'm really happy.
Sure I may have a biology project due in three hours, and I still have to make note cards for three more chapters in c&e, and my self-portrait in art is looking pretty shabby-but I got it.
I got the life.
I got the family.
And once again I got the slap in the face that my friends really do like me-enought to call at 10 and invite me to breakfast-so I need to chill.
Because I got lots a things that most people don't.

Sometimes when I'm at school and I'm with boys that I've had classes with for years I just want to kiss them, not because of a crush but just to see how good a kisser they are. 
That's what I though about all day today after exams-there were two boys in my biology class, and one in geometry class.
What can I say I'm a lipwhore, I think about kissing alot.
And if I were to kiss a boy and he were a terrible kisser and then I saw him with a girlfriend a few months later and I wouldn't be able to feel bad for her b/c of how horrible a kisser he is-b/c maybe she would like his kisses-I hope she would.
It's just another example of how I think you can't look at a couple and feel bad for the boy because the girl is annoying or has bad breath, or vice versa, because maybe he dosent think she is annoying or maybe he likes her bad breath.
Maybe Britney Spears influenced my thoughts today-she and kevin kissed on t.v. and I would have been realy excited but the camera was horrible and my dad was sitting beside me.
I hope everyone that has a boyfriend or a girlfriend likes there kisses.

Thanks to Lynn, a good movie, my sister, beads and hot glue, my mom and dad, and flea and tick shampoo I found alot this weekend.

I don't understand why I get onto myself about hurting you, I didn't do it on purpose, I made a change that I needed, I did something for myself-what you have always encouraged me to do. I'm not really sure why I talked myself out of calling to see how you are doing. I don't want you to hate me-but I understand I hurt you right now.

I love making new friends and I like the fact that I'm opening up to people more. But I'm tired of letting myself think that there is a good thing in someone, that they are the kind of person I want to get lunch with and go to the science center with and dance around on my porch while playing britney spears music. And then I realize that they're friends with everyone and there is a part of me that stops myself then. I don't know if they like me because I'm a cool person or if they like me because they like everyone.

The conclusion of the weekend is that I don't know if you hate me, and I don't know if you are going to tell your next girlfriend things about me, and I don't know if duh-duh-duh-duh-duh really likes me or if they're just treating me like they treat everyone else. But I'm not going to protect myself from everyone and experience nothing. I'd rather people tell me they don't like me than tell me they have to same emotions toward me they do everyone else.

And now that time has changed my honest people and sent them to college and Europe and insane asylums all I'm really craving is an honest friendship.

My dad and I may be in the newspaper. This makes me really happy.

I hope Elizabeth and Cory have a great weekend at the beach and I'm really happy that she and I have been talking more.

I hope that Lauren's new house is da bomb.

And I hope that this weekend is "full of explorations and wonders"(Kelcey) and that in between all the studying and cleaning and packing I can remind myself that Stephanie is home, everything is okay, and I have the entire summer to figure myself out.

I'm at this point where I'm really happy but I'm not sure what I am.

Things I am sure of:

  • Chris gets on my nerves like nobody's mom.
  • I like Britney Spears, Paris Hilton, The Olsens, Mischa Barton, Ashlee Simpson, and Jessica Simpson.
  • I love my family more than I have ever loved anything.
  • I am stronger because of the things that I have been through, and I am not old or disgusting from the experiences life has given me.
  • I didn't grow up like other kids I go to school with.
  • My first boyfriend was my mid-teenage crisis.
  • It's okay that it wasn't " the relationship".
  • I am my mothers best friend and I have more faith in her than anyone else.
  • I am amazed that we are going threw the same things at the same time.
  • My dad is my reason for morals and positive attitude.
  • He is the strongest most couragous and level headed person I know.
  • I am glad that I was raised on James Taylor, Carly Simons, the Beatles, Willy Nelson and the Eagles.
  • Sometimes I come off as mean, imature, shallow, and a class clown but I'm not.
  • I have fallen in love with two musicians.
  • I couldn't live without animals, and a farm, and getting up at 5 every morning.
  • Even though I had to live in an attic for 5 years without AC, and I spent 7 years of my life traveling for my sister, I spent 4 years studing and competing on teams that needed an extra member so she could get to state finals, and even though I wasn't there when my first horse died, and I didn't have the best friends teenagers are suppose to have.  I am happy about my childhood.
  • I miss Adam, Jamie, and Mary, and the coffee shop.
  • The best time with my sister was freshmen-senior year. Rides to school, dances, coffee shops, love.
  • I am excited about moving away from this house even though it is the best memory of christmas with a one foot tree, huricanes, leaking roofs, repairing a bathtube and the only toliet four times in one summer and the courage, strength, and determination my family has.

Fresh cut grass, bare feet, shorts, t-shirts, cook outs, guitars, pistachios, coors light, and my family are the best things in the world.

I just thought you should know that the relationship we have is the most honest, harsh, reality I have ever experienced.

And I've never been happier for you than I am now.

This is way beyond my remote concern of being condesending. 
my sister and i are so beautiful. I love ourselves together. 
she brings out the best in me and i love her more than ive ever loved anyone, because i love her with love-not fear. 

we talk about condoms, ky, and sex. we are awesome.

I am in love with your 100 year old trees, your pizza and pasta shops, your homeless me and women who are truely homeless, your dorm rooms, your lobbies, your grocery store, your cafateria, your drunk students who are funny, not discusting, your hot male students, the fact that your gender gap is shrinking, that you have awesome students. I am in hopes that by 2008 your gender gap with me 45-55 so that the boys will still be below the girls, but the pick will me easier, your ball players will be back at the top, and my GPA will be up to 4.0. Speaking of 2008, college, and a GPA I have an english paper due tomorrow and I am avoiding it like the palgue, even though I will be extremely stress free when it is over and I still have a bibliograpy and research paper to correct, a number of note cards to complete, and a work cited and research journal that haven't even seen the light of day.

Good Bye UNC basketball players. Maybe if you weren't going to the MBA I would have to motivation to complete my work. Just remeber cash-money-and hoes aren't all that is important in life. And don't forget the freshmen of 2008 when you are driving around in your jags...you will be wealthy enough to support one of us by then.

Good luck next year Noel and Roy.

Okay, so today is Easter. I've been in love with Easter sense I was a little girl, I think it was because of the cool cakes my GG made in the shapes of bunnies and eggs and pound cakes with green coconut and jelly-bellies on top. Anyway, sense my GG isn't here anymore I make the cakes and we celebrate with cousins and family friends. It's awesome, totally non-traditonal. We have food from all over the world and sense I'm the youngest kid we do have easter egg hunts, we pass a big bowl of eggs around and everyone picks and opens them together. Well this year it was a bit more adulty than i thought. I  got a condom and ky gell. which makes me wonder: what happened to the eggs? and the easter dresses? and getting all dressed up for the family pictures? and the  games we used to paly? and will i get a condom and ky for easter for the rest of my life?

ugh.

Oh! Good news, I'm moving!

Well, I hope everyone had a great easter. God bless. And have a safe spring break.
